<note id="fs-idm206319552" class="os-teacher">
<title>Facilitation Notes</title>
<para id="fs-idm525945296">This primary source can be compared to “The American Scholar” by Ralph Waldo Emerson and “Slavery in Massachusetts” by Henry David Thoreau. To compare, have students answer the following questions:</para>
<list id="fs-idm198782080" list-type="bulleted">
<item>Which transcendentalist ideologies are articulated in the works of each writer?</item>
